21:52.197 --> 21:55.603
[SPEAKER_01]: And this was when I was cutting through when I went by Aveline.

21:56.905 --> 22:00.873
[SPEAKER_01]: And he picked me up just on the other side of Aveline and driving this truck.

22:00.933 --> 22:08.526
[SPEAKER_01]: And he had been, he had hauled a load of cotton to the Galveston, I guess, from Lubbock.

22:10.109 --> 22:13.395
[SPEAKER_01]: And Lubbock, Childress, whatever.

22:16.261 --> 22:22.770
[SPEAKER_01]: He took off, and I told him I appreciated the ride, and man, he was really running it, dude.

22:24.032 --> 22:26.215
[SPEAKER_01]: But he said, can you drive a truck?

22:26.315 --> 22:28.478
[SPEAKER_01]: I said, well, I can drive a farm truck.

22:28.498 --> 22:31.001
[SPEAKER_01]: He said, well, do you have a license to drive a truck?

22:31.081 --> 22:32.904
[SPEAKER_01]: I said, no.

22:32.924 --> 22:34.286
[SPEAKER_01]: He said, I'm awfully sleepy.

22:36.068 --> 22:39.433
[SPEAKER_01]: If you could drive, I'd let you drive this thing, but I guess I'd better not.

